gomodel:SYNGO_5092  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Using the finer resolution afforded by EM (Fig. 3), CRF1-immunogold particles were primarily concentrated at asymmetric PSDs of dendritic spines, typical sites for the location of excitatory synapses. This localization of the receptor is consistent with a potentiating role of CRH on hippocampal neurotransmission.\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"For electron microscopy (EM), mice received pentobarbital at 300 mg/kg, and perfusates consisted of saline followed by a solution of 0.1% glutaraldehyde, 4% paraformaldehyde and 0.2% picric acid in 0.1 M PB. Brains were removed and postfixed in the same fixative overnight, then washed in PB.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Sections were processed for concurrent immuno-labeling of CRF1 and pCREB, as described in detail previously (Chen et al., 2001b), using goat anti-CRF1 polyclonal antiserum (1:10,000; Santa Cruz, CA, USA)\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5092" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

